\begin{align*}81^{2x} \amp= 27^{3x - 4} \\ (3^{4})^{2x} \amp= (3^{3})^{3x - 4} \\ 3^{8x} \amp= 3^{9x - 12}.\end{align*}
Now, since the bases are the same, the exponents must be equal. So we may set the exponents equal to each other and solve the resulting equation for $x$: \begin{align*}8x \amp= 9x - 12, \\ 8x - 9x \amp= -12, \\ -x \amp= -12, \\ x \amp= 12.\end{align*></think> <answer>Then $x = 12.$</answer>

